ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This outbreak seems unique in its extent, but perhaps not its
virulence. Sabah and Sarawak were perhaps spared because they are not
part of Peninsular Malaysia but are on the island of Borneo,
suggesting there isn't much trade in poultry with the mainland.
However, the breeders should not be lax regarding vaccination.
According to OIE´s Handistatus statistics, 50 outbreaks of NCD which
killed over 120 000 poultry have already been reported from Peninsular
Malaysia through April 2001:
<http://www.oie.int/hs2/zi_pays_mald.asp?c_pays=134&c_mald=17>
and there were 44 outbreaks in 2000, beginning as early as February:
<http://www.oie.int/hs2/zi_pays_mald.asp?c_pays=134&annee=2000&c_mald=
17>
- Mods. JW/TG
